headline: Prediction: Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Stock Is the Safest AI Chip Bet
summary: TSMC has become the undisputed foundry leader.  Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing (NYSE: TSM) may not design artificial intelligence (AI) chips, but it's a company that every AI chipmaker relies on.  The AI giants rely on TSMC to manufacture their number-crunching chip designs.

headline: Will a Leadership Change Be Enough to Turn Apple Around?
summary: COO Jeff Williams is retiring, and will be replaced by a 30-year Apple employee and top executive.  Apple's growth has stalled in recent years and it will be up to the new COO to make some progress.  Longtime Chief Operating Officer Jeff Williams is retiring and will be replaced by Sabih Khan, the company's senior vice president of operations.

headline: These 5 Technology Stocks Are Money-Printing Machines
summary: Large technology companies generate lots of revenue and cash flow.  Apple (NASDAQ: AAPL) has built an amazing ecosystem of consumer products and related services.  It utilized that robust cash flow and its cash-rich balance sheet (over $132 billion in cash, cash equivalents, and marketable securities) to return $29 billion to its shareholders in the quarter via dividends and share repurchases.
